<section id="overview">
      <h2>Year Overview</h2>
      <p>The Pig (<span class="chinese-char">豬</span>) occupies the Earthly Branch <strong>Hai (亥)</strong>, carrying Yang Water energy with hidden Wood. In the 2026 Fire Horse year, the Pig occupies the <strong>controlling position</strong> — Water overcomes Fire. This gives the Pig authority over the year's energy but requires constant effort to maintain that control.</p>
      <p>The Pig-Horse relationship is one of <strong>mutual tension</strong>. Fire's intensity challenges Water's tranquillity, while Water's depth threatens Fire's momentum. For the Pig, this manifests as a year where emotional equilibrium requires active maintenance — the usual ease and optimism must be consciously cultivated rather than naturally arising.</p>
      <p>The Pig's hidden Wood energy (甲 Jia within Hai) provides an important bridge — Wood mediates between Water and Fire through the generating cycle (Water→Wood→Fire). The Pig who channels energy through creative, growth-oriented pursuits (Wood activities) finds a productive pathway through the year's challenges.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="career">
      <h2>Career &amp; Finance</h2>
      <p>Career dynamics in 2026 put the Pig in a <strong>moderating and advisory role</strong>. While Fire signs charge ahead with bold plans, the Pig's Water wisdom provides essential cooling perspective. This positions the Pig as a valued counsellor, mediator, or quality-control voice — not the spotlight role, but one with significant influence.</p>
      <p><strong>Finance</strong> faces pressure from the Water-Fire dynamic. The Pig's generous nature (already the zodiac's most giving sign) is amplified by social demands, leaving less for personal savings. Setting firm financial boundaries is essential — practise saying no to lending requests and unnecessary social spending.</p>
      <p><strong>Best sectors:</strong> Healthcare, hospitality, food and beverage, social services, education, arts patronage, diplomacy, and any field where emotional intelligence and generosity are core competencies.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="love">
      <h2>Love &amp; Relationships</h2>
      <p>The Pig's romantic life in 2026 is <strong>emotionally rich but demanding</strong>. The Water-Fire dynamic creates intensity in partnerships — deep conversations, passionate exchanges, and confrontation with relationship truths. The Pig's natural desire for harmony may be challenged by necessary honest discussions.</p>
      <p><strong>Single Pigs</strong> attract partners through warmth, generosity, and genuine kindness. However, the Pig must guard against attracting those who take advantage of its giving nature. Trust instincts and allow connections to develop at a natural pace. The Rabbit month (March) and Goat month (July) bring the most harmonious romantic energy.</p>
      <p><strong>The Tiger</strong> — the Pig's Liu He secret friend — is having an outstanding 2026 (fire triangle member). This alliance provides passionate, adventurous energy that complements the Pig's nurturing nature.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="health">
      <h2>Health &amp; Wellness</h2>
      <p>The Water-Fire clash primarily affects the <strong>kidneys and urinary system</strong> (Water organs) and the <strong>heart and circulatory system</strong> (Fire organs). The Pig should monitor blood pressure, kidney function, and hydration levels throughout the year. Warm-weather months (May through August) are particularly demanding.</p>
      <p><strong>Emotional eating</strong> — the Pig's most common stress response — needs conscious management. Fire's intensity triggers comfort-seeking behaviour, and the Pig's natural appreciation for food can become excessive. Mindful eating practices, cooking as a creative outlet (rather than consumption-focused), and social meals shared with friends help maintain balance.</p>
      <p><strong>Rest and solitude</strong> are essential medicines. The Pig is naturally social, but 2026's demands require scheduled downtime. Water-element activities — bathing, swimming, walks by rivers or the ocean — restore the Pig's depleted reserves.</p>
    </section>

